	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="align(center)">
				<placeName>Warrenton</placeName>
				<date>June 24 1839</date>
			</p>
			<p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">yesterday I recd your letter<lb/> as I have not much to say in<lb/>
				<sic>regaurd</sic> of news. I will only say<lb/> that what will Please you most
				I<lb/> am far better than I have been and<lb/> your Aunt is thank God not worse<lb/>
				I think she is <sic>reather</sic> better<lb/>
				<date>Sunday</date> we shall go back to the<lb/> spring Please God and stay a 3<lb/>
				or 4 weeks so that we shall return<lb/> before <add>ט"ב</add> the spring<lb/> is one
				of best I think in this or<lb/> any other Country that is to say<lb/> the convenient
				places. and as many<lb/> Rooms to lodge 1000 people last<lb/> year there were 880
				persons there<lb/> at one time they are improving the<lb/> place with every thing
				for the<lb/> better the Company which we found<lb/> here were very
					<sic>freindly</sic> and kind, the servants very obliging, well<lb/> why should
				they not we pay them.<lb/> for <sic>there</sic> trouble. we pay $9 per<lb/> week for
				which we had 2 Herring<lb/> 4 Eggs <sic>Potatos</sic> and plenty Milk<lb/> other
				news I have none I remain</p>
			<p> Your friend xx <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Aunt send her love to you</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Remember us kindly to <persName>Mrs Couson</persName><lb/> and
				familie</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
			<p>also my friend <persName>Miss Simah Peixotto</persName>
				<persName>Mr Peixotto</persName>
				<persName>Rachel</persName><lb/> and all inquiring friends<lb/>
				<persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Mass and Charles Mass</persName> wishes to be<lb/> remembered
				to you</p>
			<p rend="align(center)">The Revd</p>
			<p rend="align(center)indent(2)">
				<persName>Isaac Leeser</persName>
			</p>
			<p rend="align(center)indent(2)">
				<placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
			</p>
		</body>
